title: For Sale:  HK Factory Nickel P7M13, NIB, Rare
postcontent: Up for SALE is a very rare NIB factory nickel HK P7M13. As you will see, this gun is in museum grade condition. It would be impossible to find another one such condition. This gun was part of an HK collection from a collector who bought it new in 1993. That collector went into retirement, and liquidated some very rare guns last summer. I purchased this gun from him, within hours of it becoming available. This gun has spent the last 23 years in a time capsule. A climate controlled capsule. Rarely handled, let alone fired. Even the mags have never been loaded (hence the photo detailing the mag follower). Everything about it is as new as new gets. When I took ownership of it last summer, I continued its preservation with a climate controlled safe of my own. As tempting as it is to handle and admire, I’ve done my best to avoid doing so. Mainly due to the extensive storage preparation required after handling. Heck I’ve even avoided touching/opening the factory box it comes in. I doubt one could find a 23 year old gun box without scratches, as if it was manufactured yesterday. To preserve everything to my utmost ability, I bag sealed the box, then foam wrapped the bagged box to eliminate any chance of the box getting scratched.  So to the HK collector out there, here is your chance to have a pristine example of the factory nickel P7M13.
